  "response": "Here are some effective ways to manage and reduce acne:\n\n1. Skincare routine\n- Cleanse face twice daily\n- Use non-comedogenic products\n- Avoid touching your face\n- Use gentle, oil-free moisturizers\n\n2. Over-the-counter treatments\n- Benzoyl peroxide\n- Salicylic acid\n- Retinol creams\n- Tea tree oil\n\n3. Lifestyle changes\n- Maintain a healthy diet\n- Stay hydrated\n- Get enough sleep\n- Manage stress\n- Exercise regularly\n\n4. Professional treatments\n- Prescription topical medications\n- Oral antibiotics\n- Chemical peels\n- Laser therapy\n- Cortisone injections\n\n5. Avoid\n- Heavy makeup\n- Picking or squeezing pimples\n- Harsh scrubbing\n- Greasy or sugary foods\n\n6. Natural remedies\n- Aloe vera\n- Green tea extract\n- Zinc supplements\n\n7. For severe cases\n- Consult a dermatologist\n- Consider prescription medications like Accutane\n\nThe best approach often involves a combination of these methods, tailored to your specific skin type and acne severity.",
